COLOMBO , July 29 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- A moderate Tamil parliamentarian and three others including the suicide bomber were killed in a suicide bombing Thursday morning in the capital of Sri Lanka , informed sources said .
N. Thiruchelvam of the Tamil United Liberation Front -LRB- TULF -RRB- and two others were inside a car when a suicide bomber riding a motorcycle attacked them , the sources said .
The four people died on the spot , the sources said .
Thiruchelvam is a leading Tamil leader who favors political solution and cooperation to solve the long-standing ethnic conflicts in the country .
No people or groups have yet claimed responsibility for the bombing .
But the police suspect that it is the work of separatist Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam -LRB- LTTE -RRB- to mark the Black July anniversary .
LTTE rebels have been fighting the Sri Lankan government for an independent Tamil homeland in the north and east of the country since the Black July of 1983 which saw bloody and violent ethnic clashes between majority Sinhalese and minority Tamils .
